-- 55. Date Functions in MYSQL:-

1. NOW() Function:-
-- used to get the current date and time.

-- Select NOW().
-- Result:-2022-11-12 18:59:16.


2. CURDATE() Function:-
-- Used to get the current date without the time component.

-- Select CURDATE();
-- Result:-2022-11-12.


3. CURTIME() Function:-
-- Used to get the current time without the date component.

---- Select CURTIME();
-- Result:-19:02:14.


NOTE:- We have some functions which are used to get
-- the specific information from the now function.


4. YEAR(NOW()), MONTH(NOW()),DAY(NOW()),HOUR(NOW()),MINUTE(NOW()),SECOND(NOW()) Function:-
-- These all functions are used to get specific information from 
-- the now function like month, day, hour etc.


5.DAYNAME(NOW()) and MONTHNAME(NOW()) Function:-
-- These return strings as result , current month name or current day name.


6.Extract() Function:-
-- This function is used to extract a piece of information from some function like Year, Month, Day, Hour, Minute, Second.


-- Select Extract(Month from Now());
-- Result:-11.





-- EXERCISE:-
-- Get the orders placed in the current year. Consider current year=2019.

